com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport

Class AmendCardOnItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.Command
      • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.AmendCardOnItem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICommand, IItemChangeSetCommand, IChangeSet<CardChangeSet,CardChangeSet>, IItemChangeSet

    public final class AmendCardOnItem
extends Command
implements IItemChangeSetCommand
    The IItemChangeSetCommand for amending a Card (as defined by a CardChangeSet) on an Item.

    If the CardChangeSet.getSourceInfo() method returns null, then the amended Card's SourceInfo is not changed.

    Leasing:

    • An active lease must exist on the Item containing the Card to be amended.
    Authorization:
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for the Item.
    Validation:
    • The Item must not already be marked as deleted.
    • The Item must not have been the source of a merge.
    • The CardChangeSet must contain no CardProvenance.
    • The CardChangeSets must contain no Propertys or PropertyGroups that have ProhibitedCreate associated with their types.
    • The CardChangeSets must contain no PropertyChanges or PropertyGroupChanges that have ProhibitedEdit associated with their property or property group types.
    • See CardChangeSet for more validation rules.
    Since:
    1.0
